Ezentis Aims to Become Investor Such as Alba, Expansion Reports

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-12-01T08:17:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-01/ezentis-aims-to-become-investor-such-as-alba-expansion-reports.html
Grupo Ezentis SA (EZE)  aims to become an
investor group similar to Corp. Financiera Alba and expects to
collaborate with  Telefonica SA (TEF)  in  Latin America , Ezentis
Chairman Manuel Garcia-Duran told  Expansion  in an interview.  Ezentis, which reached an agreement yesterday to sell its
infrastructure unit Sedesa to Vicente Cotino, will now focus on
good potential investments, Garcia-Duran said, according to the
newspaper.  Ezentis considers its 29 percent stake in  Vertice
Trescientos Sesenta Grados SA (VER)  as strategic for the company, he
said, Expansion reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
